Package com.team7.cmput301.android.theirisproject.task

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Callback<M>
    Callback is an interface that allows AsyncTasks to call functions from the main thread after the async task is finished.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddBodyPhotoTask
    AddBodyPhotoTask asynchronously adds bodyphotos to the database
    AddCommentTask
    AddCommentTask adds a comment asynchronously on another thread and will return the result status: success or error
    AddPatientTask
    AddPatientTask takes in two parameters, the Patient's e-mail that the Care Provider inputted and the Care Provider's ID.
    AddProblemTask
    AddProblemTask is an AsyncTask that sends a POST request to our database with the new problem data.
    AddRecordTask
    AddRecordTask is an async task that will dispatch when the user submits a new record and the task will add it to the database returning its id
    DeleteProblemTask
    DeleteProblemTask asynchronously deletes a problem from the database
    EditProblemTask
    EditProblemTask is an AsyncTask that sends a POST request to our database with the edited problem data.
    GetPatientListTask
    GetPatientListTask is responsible for taking in a careProviderId and returning a List of Patients representing all Patients that Care Provider has registered.
    GetProblemListTask
    GetProblemListTask is a function that asynchronously retrieves data from our Elasticsearch database.
    GetProblemTask
    GetProblemTask asynchronously gets a problem from the database first it queries the primitive fields of a problem.
    GetRecordListTask
    Asynchronously searches ElasticSearch DB to ultimately make a RecordList
    GetRecordTask
    GetRecordTask is an async task that fetches a Record model from the database given a record id
    GetUserDataTask
    Asynchronously gets all of a User's data.
    LoginTask  
    RegisterTask
    RegisterTask is an AsyncTask that asynchronously registers the given user into the database.
